                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                                        <date>Set 27<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Dear Friend <addressee>Isaac</addressee>,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I again trouble you, with<lb/> a few lines, to\n                                        inquire if I, cannot have my<lb/> Books for <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">Roshashona</hi>, as I have only\n                                        one book for<lb/> those days; if they cannot be completed by\n                                        then<lb/> if you have any with <persName>Theodore\n                                                  Seixsas</persName>, can I have<lb/> them\n                                                  <sic>untill</sic> mine, are ready?—are you\n                                        coming<lb/> on soon, I suppose not if report says true<lb/>\n                                        you are better employed attending your <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >new</hi> flame<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mrs D C Levy's</persName> sister, you are a\n                                        cunning fellow and<lb/> mean to take us by surprise, but\n                                        that you'll<lb/> never do with me for I am always\n                                        expecting<lb/> some such event for I well know you will\n                                        marry<lb/> when you see the <hi rend=\"underline\">miss\n                                                  right</hi> or the right miss—I will not send<lb/>\n                                        you any more commissions, as Love, regards &amp;c<lb/> since\n                                        I meet with no return—I had the<lb/> pleasure of a visit\n                                        from <persName>Andrew Cohen</persName>, he is fine<lb/>\n                                        looking and amiable young man—<persName>Theodore\n                                                  Florence</persName><lb/> came to see me how he has\n                                        grown, quite a <hi rend=\"underline\">bean</hi><lb/>\n                                                  too—<persName>Eleanor</persName>, &amp;\n                                                  <persName>Sarah</persName>, are both engaged, the\n                                        one<lb/> to <persName>Abraham Jonas'</persName> eldest son\n                                                  <persName>Charles</persName>, and\n                                                  <persName>Eleanor</persName><lb/> to\n                                                  <persName>Henno Labatt</persName> now of\n                                                  <placeName>California</placeName>, I am quite<lb/>\n                                        satisfied with them both, they are men of worth,<lb/> still\n                                        I do not like <persName>Eleanor's</persName> having to go to\n                                                  <placeName>California</placeName><lb/> but he\n                                        promises to remain only 4 or 5 years—<lb/> have you heard it\n                                        before? if not do not speak of</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rn30q6t/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
